Purchasing Options\
\
	on demand			-		short workload, uninterrupted\
								predictable pricing, pay by second, highest cost, no upfront payment, no long term commitment\
								use case - you don\'92t know how the application will behave\
	reserved				-		long workloads (1 and 3 years)\
								~70% discount compared to on demand, reservation period is specified, payment can be no upfront, partial upfront or all upfront\
								specific instance attributes are reserved (instance type, region, tenancy, OS) and the instance reservation scope is regional or zonal\
								buy and sell in the Reserved Instance Marketplace\
								use case - steady state applications (database)\
	convertible reserved		-		long workloads with flexible instances\
								like a reserved instance but you can change the instance type, instance family, OS, scope and tenancy\
								~66% discount compared to on demand\
	Savings plan			-		long workloads (1 andd 3 years)\
								commitment to an amount of usage (e.g. $10/hour for 1 or 3 years)\
								usage beyond the savings plan is billed at On Demand price\
								locked to a specific instance family  and region (e.g. M5 in us-east-1) but flexible across size and OS and tenancy\
	Spot Instances			-		short workloads\
								~90% discount compared to on demand\
								can lose instance (less reliable) if your max price is less than current spot price\
								CHEAPEST OPTION\
								use case - workloads that are resilient to failure (batch jobs, data analysis, image processing, distributed workloads)\
	dedicated host			-		book an entire physical server\
								control instance placement\
								can be purchased on demand or reserved\
								MOST EXPENSIVE OPTION\
								use case - compliance requirements (e.g. server bound software licenses on per socket, per-core, per VM)\
	dedicated instance		-		an instance that runs on hardware dedicated to you\
								no other customers will share your hardware\
								other instances in the same account can share the hardware\
								no control over instance placement (can move hardware after start or stop)\
	capacity reservation		-		reserve on-demand instances capacity in a specific AZ for any duration\
								you always have access to EC2 capacity when you need it\
								no time commitment (create/cancel any time)\
								no billing discounts\
								combine with regional reserved instances and savings plans to benefit from billing discounts\
								you\'92re charged at on-demand rate whether you run instances or not\
								use case - short term uninterrupted workloads that need to be in a specific AZ\
\
