Storage Tiers:\
	Standard\
\
\
Storage Options:\
\
EBS					-	Elastic Block Store	 	storing data on virtual drives\
\
think of it as a network drive\
good but limited performance\
used for data persistence even after instance has terminated\
only be mounted to one instance at a time\
they are bound to a specific AZ\
Snapshot\
	archive			-	ebs snapshot can be moved to an archive tier - about 75% cheaper\
						but takes 24 to 72 hours for restoring from the archive\
	recycle bin		-	rules to retain deleted snapshots so you can recover, retention period needs to be specified from 1 day to 1 year\
\
\
EC2 Instance Store\
\
high performance hardware disk \
when you need better IO performance\
ephemeral (storage is lost if they are stopped)\
risk of data loss if hardware fails (so you need to take care of backups)\
use case - buffer, cache, scratch data, temporary content\
\
\
\
EFS					-	Elastic File Storage		Managed NFS\
\
managed NFS that can be mounted on 100s of EC2 instances\
works only with Linux EC2 instances\
multi AZ capable\
highly available, scalable, expensive (3 x gp2), pay per amount of storage, no need to capacity plan\
EFS-IA  -  EFS infrequent Access is a storage class that is cost-optimized for file not accessed every day (around 92% less cost)\
\
